target_text: Trump returned to the White House on Monday evening and is receiving treatment for the disease amid concerns that he remains contagious and could infect people inside the White House complex

More than a dozen people who have been around Trump in recent days have tested positive for Covid-19, many of whom attended the White House ceremony for Supreme Court nominee Amy Coney Barrett on Sept. 26
Two more White House residence staff tested positive for Covid-19 nearly three weeks ago, a White House official confirmed
None of the four came into contact with the first family, the official said, and all of them wore masks
On Wednesday, the president returned to the Oval Office and released a video declaring himself essentially "cured" of Covid-19
White House physician Dr. Sean Conley said earlier this week that they wouldn't know whether he was out of the woods until after this weekend
